                        <h2>FAQ</h2>
                        <h3>
                           What is an assignment?
                        </h3>
                        <p>
                           An assignment is when a Seller sells their interest in a property before they take possession – in simpler language; Seller is selling the contract they have with the Builder.
                        </p>
                        <h3>Do assignments are only for pre-construction?</h3>
                        <p>
                            Technically Assignment can be done for any type of property, pre-construction or resale, As long as it is allowed by Seller/Builder. What we offer as service to buyers and sellers is Pre-construction Condos, Semis, Detach and Town-Homes.
                        </p>
                        <h3>Why seller wants to assign Pre-construction property?</h3>
                        <p>
                            It can be any of the following reasons:
Seller's circumstances changed…new job, got married or engaged, got kids, etc. What was a good property then is not suitable now.
Seller may have financial problems currently and it may not be possible for them to close with builder.
Price has appreciated since seller booked with builder and seller wants to cash in seller's profit.
                        </p>
                        <h3>Assignment Fee by Builder</h3>
                        <p>
                           When builders allow for assignment, it may or may not have assignment fee. Who pays this fee? It is negotiable between buyer and seller.
                        </p>
                        <h3>Marketing Restrictions</h3>
                        <p>
                           Some Builders do not allow the marketing of an assignment… Builder will give right to assign but will put restriction marketing for example You can advertise on Social media, online or MLS. This brings us in picture, with data base of Buyer and Sellers interested in Assignment, we make this sale possible.
                        </p>
                        <h3>What are the tax implications of assignment?</h3>
                        <p>
                           Please take tax advice from a certified accountant. 
                        </p>
                        <h3>How does the closing work?</h3>
                        <p>
                           There are 2 closings: the closing between the Original Buyer and new buyer and between Builder and New Buyer. There will be three lawyers involved representing Original Buyer, New Buyer and Builder.
                        </p>
                        <h3>What is interim closing?</h3>
                        <p>The interim closing usually happen in condos. When the unit is ready for possession buy Condominium Corporation is not registered yet.
During the interim occupancy, Buyer occupies the unit and pays occupancy fee. 
</p>
                        
                        
                     

